  malvinas day was first introduced on 22 november 2000 , and replaced the " day of argentine sovereignty over the malvinas , sandwich and south atlantic islands " ( día de los derechos argentinos sobre las islas malvinas , sandwich y del atlántico sur ) observed on 10 june , which had until then commemorated the appointment by buenos aires of luis vernet as governor of the islands in 1829.el 2 de abril volvio a ser feriado , como en   la dictadura : derechos , humanos y soberanos pagina 12 , 2 april 2001   malvinas day is not observed in the falklands , although a related holiday called liberation day is celebrated on 14 june to mark the end of the war .

holidays : this country observes june 10 as malvinas day

